    "chemicalDescription": [
      "s-Cannabis Sativa Octapeptide-1 is a single chain peptide consisting of glycine, isoleucine, leucine, phenylalanine, threonine and tryptophan. It is synthetically produced based on a sequence from Cytochrome c Biogenesis Protein CcsA which is found in Cannabis sativa. The parent protein contains a maximum of 320 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation."
